  {"a":"warwick","b":"poppy","win":["Warwick","Skill","Warwick","Warwick","Warwick","Warwick","Poppy"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Your Q heal and Blood Hunt speed win extended trades before Poppy is tanky; bait her Heroic Charge so she can't pin you to a wall for the stun."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Infinite Duress locks Poppy down and bursts her — just be ready for her to Keeper's Verdict cancel your engage; all-in when her W and R are down."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With a bruiser item and level lead you out-duel Poppy cleanly since her tank damage hasn't scaled and your Jaws sustain grinds her down."},{"when":"Late","text":"Poppy's full tank build plus Steadfast Presence dash-block and Keeper's Verdict knockback make her a slippery, unkillable peeler who wins the late duel."}],"wants":{"you":["Win the lane early while her tank damage is low and yours is high","Avoid walls so her Heroic Charge can't stun you against terrain","All-in when Steadfast Presence and Keeper's Verdict are on cooldown"],"foe":["Reach tank items where her HP shrugs off your on-hit damage","Pin you to a wall with Heroic Charge for the extended stun","Cancel your Infinite Duress engage with Keeper's Verdict knockback"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are yours — Poppy has weak early damage and just wants to farm, so trade with Q, sustain her poke, and mark her with Blood Hunt when she drops low.","mid":"Levels 3 to 6 firmly favour you: your Q reset and W speed win every trade before she stacks armor, and Infinite Duress at 6 bursts her; just avoid walls so Heroic Charge can't pin and stun you.","late":"Past two tank items Poppy flips it — her HP outscales your on-hit, Steadfast Presence blocks your dashes and grounds you, and Keeper's Verdict can cancel your all-in, so don't solo her once she's fully built.","whys":["Level 1 favours you because Poppy has feeble early damage and only wants to farm.","Level 2 is even as both build toward a spike with no decisive combo yet.","Level 3 favours you: Q reset and Blood Hunt speed out-trade her weak early kit.","Levels 4-5 stay yours since your sustain and burst beat her low tank damage.","Level 6 is yours because Infinite Duress bursts her before her tank stats matter.","First item favours you as your bruiser spike beats a tank whose damage hasn't scaled.","Two-plus items swings to Poppy: full tank HP, dash-block, and knockback win the late duel."]},
  {"a":"warwick","b":"quinn","win":["Warwick","Skill","Warwick","Quinn","Warwick","Quinn","Quinn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"With Q for the leash-heal and E to cancel her Vault, you can force short trades she can't sustain through — walk her down while your passive ticks and Blood Hunt speed keeps you glued to her."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Infinite Duress ignores her Vault knockback and her E's dash-away; ult her the instant she blinds you and you win the all-in outright."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Once she finishes a lethality item and hits her Blinding Assault (Q) into Vault (E) reset combo cleanly, her burst and disengage outrange your gap-close."},{"when":"Late","text":"Quinn roams and one-shots squishies with Heightened Senses; if she's ahead she kites your R with Vault and Skystrike, so group and force her onto your frontline."}],"wants":{"you":["Land R after she burns Vault (E) so she can't dash out","Use E Primal Howl to eat her Blinding Assault windup","Perma-shove and dive her before she stacks lethality"],"foe":["Poke you flat with Blinding Assault every cooldown","Vault backward the moment you E or dash in","Roam mid/bot with her ult while you're stuck top"]},"early":"Level 1-2 you out-stat her — she's a marksman with no early sustain, so hug the wave and punish any auto with a Q reset. Her only trade tool is Blinding Assault (Q), which greys out your autos but not your ability damage.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay yours until she blinks in items: your E cancels her Vault engage and Q keeps you topped, and at 6 Infinite Duress channels through her blind to lock her down. Bait the Vault, then commit.","late":"After her first lethality item Quinn's poke and one-combo burst spike hard — she blinds, Vaults away, and kites your R. Keep sidelanes shoved and only engage when her E is down.","whys":["You out-stat a level-1 marksman with your passive heal and dueling base kit.","Even early skirmish — her Blinding Assault trades against your sustain, neither snowballs.","You out-duel her at 3 with Q sustain and E to eat her Vault engage.","Her Blinding Assault plus Vault reset out-poke and disengage your commit through 4-5.","Infinite Duress channels through her blind and ignores Vault, so 6 flips back to you.","Her first lethality item turns Blinding Assault into real burst she can kite behind.","Item Quinn out-ranges and out-roams you, blinding and Vaulting away from your all-in."]},
  {"a":"warwick","b":"renekton","win":["Warwick","Renekton","Renekton","Skill","Warwick","Renekton","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"This is Renekton's window: with full fury he dashes in with Ruthless Predator (W) stun, Cull the Meek (Q) heal, and Dice (E) resets — he out-trades and out-sustains you badly before 6."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Infinite Duress is your equaliser — his W stun is point-blank and his empowered W only stuns while it's up, so ult when his fury is empty and he can't cancel your channel."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With a completed bruiser item and fury back online Renekton's double-E Dice mobility and W stun let him pick the trade and disengage yours."},{"when":"Late","text":"Renekton falls off relative to your scaling; even at parity his all-in needs fury and E charges, so bait those and R him when they're spent."}],"wants":{"you":["Ult him when his fury bar is empty and W can't stun-cancel you","Trade at 6+ where Blood Hunt and R flip his fury advantage","Freeze near your tower so his short E dashes can't safely engage"],"foe":["Fury-stack then all-in with W stun into Q heal","Use both E Dice charges to dodge your Q and reset trades","Kill you 3-5 before you hit your R spike"]},"early":"Level 1 you're fine — pre-fury Renekton has no stun and your passive out-sustains his slap. Don't feed him fury; poke minions, not him.","mid":"Levels 2-5 are his: full-fury Ruthless Predator (W) point-blank stuns you out of everything while Cull the Meek (Q) heals him through your damage and Dice (E) resets his engage. Respect the stun and give ground until 6.","late":"At 6 Infinite Duress flips it — channel him when his fury is empty so W can't interrupt. Past first items it's fury-dependent skill: bait his E charges and W, then commit your R.","whys":["Pre-fury level 1 you out-sustain his slap with no stun on the board yet.","At 2 his Ruthless Predator stun and Cull the Meek heal out-trade you.","Full-fury 3-5 is Renekton's peak — W stun, Q heal, E resets dominate.","Even window at 4-5 as your R comes online against his fading fury lead.","Infinite Duress locks him when his fury and W stun are spent — your spike.","With items his fury-fuelled W stun and double-E mobility pick trades again.","Late game is skill and fury management — his all-in versus your R timing even out."]},
  {"a":"warwick","b":"riven","win":["Warwick","Riven","Riven","Riven","Riven","Riven","Riven"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Once Riven has all three Broken Wings (Q) charges plus Valor (E) shield and Ki Burst (W) stun, she animation-cancels burst that shreds you and her mobility ignores your gap-close."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Even at 6 she can Valor-dash and Q away from your Infinite Duress windup, and her R execute punishes you low — ult only if her E is already down."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With a first bruiser/lethality item her three-Q into W stun into R combo simply one-rotations you before Blood Hunt matters."},{"when":"Late","text":"Riven's mobility and burst stay ahead of your all-in; only catch her when Valor (E) and her Q charges are spent."}],"wants":{"you":["Bait out Valor (E) and all three Q charges before you engage","Only R her when her E dash is on cooldown","Farm safe and scale — look for jungle collapses, not solo kills"],"foe":["Q-Q-Q into W Ki Burst stun to lock and burst you","Valor-shield your trade damage and dash out of your R","Snowball early leads with her level-3 all-in"]},"early":"Level 1 you edge her with passive sustain before she has her combo online, so contest the first wave. It's the only phase you're favoured — don't overstay it.","mid":"Levels 2 onward belong to Riven: full Broken Wings (Q) charges, Ki Burst (W) stun and Valor (E) shield let her animation-cancel a burst combo that out-trades you, and her mobility dodges your engage. Play for farm and jungle pressure.","late":"With items her Q-W-R combo one-rotations you and her E keeps her out of Infinite Duress range. Never solo-commit unless her Valor is down; scale and group.","whys":["Level 1 you out-sustain her before her Q charges and combo come online.","At 2 her Ki Burst stun and Broken Wings burst start out-trading you.","Full-charge level-3 Riven out-bursts and out-mobilities you hard.","Her Valor shield and Q dashes let her dodge your commit through 4-5.","At 6 she Valor-dashes out of Infinite Duress and R-executes you low.","Her first item makes the Q-W-R combo a clean one-rotation kill.","Late-game Riven's mobility and burst stay ahead of your all-in every fight."]},
  {"a":"warwick","b":"rumble","win":["Rumble","Skill","Rumble","Rumble","Rumble","Rumble","Rumble"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"In the Danger Zone Rumble's Flamespitter (Q) melts you while Scrap Shield (E) and the Electro Harpoon (E) slow keep you at range — his heat-boosted rotation out-DPSes your all-in."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"The Equalizer (R) zones your entire engage path; he drops it between you and him and your Infinite Duress can't cross it safely."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With Liandry's/Haestem online his Flamespitter and Harpoon do percent-health burn that beats your sustain no matter how long the fight runs."},{"when":"Late","text":"Rumble's overheated Flamespitter plus Equalizer keep him ahead — only threaten him when his heat is redlined and Q/shield are down."}],"wants":{"you":["Engage only when Rumble is Overheated and silenced","Save E Primal Howl to reduce his Flamespitter and ult damage","Look for jungle ganks — you can't solo this lane"],"foe":["Sit in the Danger Zone and boosted-Flamespitter you down","Slow you with Electro Harpoon and peel with Scrap Shield","Drop The Equalizer across your all-in path"]},"early":"Level 1 is close but heat-dependent — before Rumble builds heat you can walk up, but the moment he hits the Danger Zone his Q burns you. Don't trust the calm.","mid":"Levels 3-6 are all Rumble: boosted Flamespitter (Q) melts you, Scrap Shield (E) and the Harpoon slow kite your dashes, and heat management lets him win any extended trade against your sustain. Farm from range.","late":"Liandry's-boosted burn plus The Equalizer (R) zoning keep him ahead through items. Engage only when he's Overheated and silenced, and lean on jungle pressure to break the lane.","whys":["Danger-Zone Flamespitter out-burns you even at level 1 once his heat is up.","Even skill window at 2 before his boosted Q rotation fully comes online.","Boosted Flamespitter plus Harpoon slow out-DPS and kite you at 3.","His Scrap Shield and heat-managed Q keep beating your trades through 4-5.","The Equalizer zones your engage path the moment he hits 6.","Liandry's percent-burn on his Q out-sustains you after his first item.","Overheat-managed Flamespitter and Equalizer keep Rumble ahead all game."]},
  {"a":"warwick","b":"ryze","win":["Warwick","Warwick","Warwick","Skill","Warwick","Warwick","Warwick"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Ryze is immobile and squishy — with Q Jaws to close and E Primal Howl to cut his Overload (Q) poke, you walk him down and force flash before he outscales."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Infinite Duress channels through his Rune Prison (W) root attempt if you ult first; land R and he has no dash or blink to escape you."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Even with Rod/Tear online Ryze has zero mobility to your all-in — Blood Hunt speed plus R runs him down the moment his W root is on cooldown."},{"when":"Late","text":"Ryze scales but stays escape-less in lane; keep him shoved and dive him whenever Rune Prison (W) is down and your R is up."}],"wants":{"you":["Walk him down when Rune Prison (W) is on cooldown","R through his root and burst him with no escape available","Perma-shove and threaten all-in so he can never freely poke"],"foe":["Root you with Rune Prison then kite with Overload spam","Poke you with Q Overload from max range","Survive to teamfights where his Realm Warp scales"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are yours — Ryze has no early kill pressure and no mobility, so you walk up behind minions and threaten every time his Overload (Q) is on cooldown. Punish his short range with your reach.","mid":"Levels 3-6 you dominate: Q Jaws closes the gap, E Primal Howl blunts his Overload poke and reduces his burst, and at 6 Infinite Duress locks down an escape-less mage. Force him to flash or die.","late":"Ryze wants to scale, but in lane he never gets safe — keep the wave shoved into him and all-in whenever Rune Prison (W) is down. Blood Hunt plus R guarantee you catch him.","whys":["You out-range his kill threat at 1 and punish his cooldowns with your reach.","At 2 he still has no mobility and no way to stop you walking him down.","Level 3 Q-and-E let you close and shred an immobile, squishy mage.","Even window at 4-5 as he can trade Overload poke into your engage windows.","Infinite Duress locks an escape-less Ryze the moment you hit 6.","With items he's still mobility-less — your R and Blood Hunt run him down.","Even late he can't escape your all-in in lane whenever his W is on cooldown."]},
  {"a":"warwick","b":"sejuani","win":["Warwick","Skill","Warwick","Skill","Skill","Warwick","Warwick"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Sejuani is a tank with weak lane damage — with Q Jaws sustain and Blood Hunt you out-DPS her Arctic Assault (Q) and can shove and threaten before her Frost Armor (E) stacks matter."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her Glacial Prison (R) is a skillshot stun; if she lands it first she can lock your combo, so bait it — this is the even, skill-check window."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Once you have a bruiser item your sustained damage beats her tank stats one-v-one; her E Permafrost slow just tickles and she can't kill you."},{"when":"Late","text":"Sejuani becomes a teamfight engage tool, not a duelist — solo you shred her, but respect her R catching you for a jungle collapse."}],"wants":{"you":["Bait Glacial Prison (R) before you commit your all-in","Out-sustain her weak lane damage and shove for plates","Duel her post-item where your DPS beats her tank stats"],"foe":["Land Glacial Prison (R) to stun-lock your combo","Stack Frost Armor (E) and slow you with Permafrost","Roam and engage for her jungler with her CC"]},"early":"Level 1 is yours — Sejuani has almost no lane damage and your passive out-sustains her Arctic Assault (Q) poke. Push the wave and set up plate pressure.","mid":"Levels 2-5 are a mix: at 3 you shove and out-DPS her tanky-but-toothless kit, but her Frost Armor (E) and Permafrost slow plus her impending R make the 4-5 window a skill check. Don't walk into a point-blank Glacial Prison.","late":"From 6 on you're favoured again — bait her R, then Infinite Duress and your item DPS shred her tank stats one-v-one. She's an engage tool late, so watch for her setting up ganks rather than dueling.","whys":["You out-sustain Sejuani's near-zero level-1 lane damage with your passive.","Even skill window at 2 as her Arctic Assault and armor stacks come online.","At 3 you shove and out-DPS her tanky but low-damage kit.","Her Frost Armor and Permafrost slow make the 4-5 trade a wash.","Her Glacial Prison stun is a coin-flip skillshot the moment she hits 6.","Post-item your bruiser DPS beats her tank stats in a straight duel.","Late solo you shred her — she's an engage tool, not a duelist."]},
  {"a":"warwick","b":"sett","win":["Warwick","Skill","Warwick","Skill","Warwick","Warwick","Sett"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Sett's Haymaker (W) grit-shield needs to bank damage first — trade in short bursts with Q Jaws so you empty your combo before he punches, and your sustain wins the exchange."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Infinite Duress locks him before he can land Facebreaker (E) grab or true-damage Haymaker; ult him when his W shield is empty and you win the all-in."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your Blood Hunt uptime and Q sustain still out-duel him after first items — just don't feed his W by trading into a full grit bar."},{"when":"Late","text":"Sett scales into a bruiser monster: full-build Haymaker true damage plus The Show Stopper (R) suplex flip the duel, so kite his cooldowns and fight with your jungler."}],"wants":{"you":["Trade in bursts so his Haymaker (W) grit bar stays empty","R him at 6 before he lands Facebreaker (E) or W","Duel him early where your sustain beats his grit shield"],"foe":["Bank grit then unload a true-damage Haymaker (W)","Facebreaker (E) stun you and R-suplex you out of position","Scale into his late-game bruiser stats and out-tank you"]},"early":"Level 1 you edge him — before Sett has grit banked his slap is weak and your passive out-sustains it. Push and threaten while his Haymaker (W) is empty.","mid":"Levels 3-6 favour you: trade in bursts so his grit bar never fills, use E Primal Howl to blunt his punch, and at 6 Infinite Duress locks him before Facebreaker (E) or Haymaker land. Empty your combo, then back off before he reloads grit.","late":"Sett out-scales you — a full-build true-damage Haymaker (W) and The Show Stopper (R) suplex turn the duel his way after two-plus items. Respect his grit, kite his E, and bring your jungler for the kill.","whys":["Pre-grit level-1 Sett has a weak slap you out-sustain with your passive.","Even skill window at 2 as his Haymaker grit bar begins to matter.","At 3 your burst trades keep his grit empty and your sustain wins.","His banked-grit Haymaker versus your burst trades even out at 4-5.","Infinite Duress locks him before Facebreaker or Haymaker land at 6.","Your Blood Hunt uptime and Q sustain still out-duel him at first item.","Full-build Sett out-tanks you and his true-damage W plus R suplex win."]},
  {"a":"warwick","b":"shen","win":["Warwick","Skill","Warwick","Warwick","Warwick","Skill","Shen"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"With W Blood Hunt active you outrun Shen's slow and Q Jaws of the Beast heal on his own minions to full-clear his poke; punish every wave he uses Twilight Assault (Q) to shove instead of trade."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R Infinite Duress locks Shen out of Spirit's Refuge (W) and Shadow Dash (E) — ult him mid-CS and you burst him before he can block or dash back to tower."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Even at your first-item spike a fed Shen can Stand United (R) bot for a kill, so track his ult timer; the lane goes Skill here because you win the duel but he wins map value."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late game Shen out-tanks your DPS with Sunfire plus his Q shield and passive, and his global ult swings teamfights — you fall behind unless you snowballed the solo kills."}],"wants":{"you":["Bait Shen to shove so W speed lets you all-in on cooldown","Save R for after his E Shadow Dash is on the floor","Roam or invade with your jungler when his R is down"],"foe":["Use E Shadow Dash to peel your R and taunt you off","Farm safe under tower with Q on minions for the shield","Press R Stand United to save a bot lane and get ahead globally"]},"early":"Level 1 you win the bush and can Q-tick him down, so start strong and deny his Q energy sustain. By level 2 it's Skill — Shen's Q shield off minions blunts your early poke if he plays it right.","mid":"Levels 3-6 are yours: Blood Hunt speed catches him whenever he steps up, and Q healing off his minions keeps you topped through his poke. Land R at 6 and he can't Shadow Dash or Spirit's Refuge out of the burst.","late":"First item you still win the raw 1v1, but Shen's global R and stacking tank items tilt the lane back to Skill and then to Shen — he becomes a peel-and-teamfight problem your solo damage can't answer.","whys":["Level 1 favours you: Warwick wins the bush duel and Q-ticks Shen before he has energy sustain.","Level 2 is skill: Shen's Q shield off minions can neutralize your early poke if timed well.","Level 3 favours you: W Blood Hunt speed catches Shen every time he steps up to CS.","Levels 4-5 favour you: sustained Q healing off his minions keeps you healthy through Shen's poke.","Level 6 favours you: R Infinite Duress ignores his E dash and W refuge, letting you burst him down.","First item is skill: you win the duel but Shen's global R Stand United starts generating map value.","2+ items favour Shen: his tank stats and teamfight ult outscale your single-target DPS."]},
  {"a":"warwick","b":"singed","win":["Warwick","Skill","Warwick","Warwick","Warwick","Singed","Singed"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"W Blood Hunt speed lets you stick to Singed as he Fling-and-runs, and Q healing counters his Poison Trail chip — chase him off the wave whenever his Fling (Q) is down."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R Infinite Duress is a hard channel that keeps him in place despite Mega Adhesive (W) and his Insanity Potion (R) speed — burst him before he kites into your minions."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Once Singed hits Rylai's/Rush of Rod he proxies your wave and out-scales the duel; the lane flips to him because you can no longer catch the slippery poison monster."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late Singed is a permanent chase-me nuisance with Fling flips, huge HP, and Mega Adhesive slows — your R gets baited or Flung and you can't kill him fast enough."}],"wants":{"you":["All-in while your W speed out-paces his Insanity Potion","Use R when his Fling (Q) and Mega Adhesive (W) are down","Freeze near your tower so he can't proxy safely"],"foe":["Fling (Q) you into his tower or his jungler","Drop Mega Adhesive (W) to slow your W chase and root you","Proxy waves and scale with Rylai's to kite you forever"]},"early":"Level 1 you win: your Q ticks beat his early Poison Trail and he has no Fling yet to flip you away. Level 2 is Skill — his poison starts to matter but you still hold tempo.","mid":"Levels 3-6 belong to you. Blood Hunt speed closes the gap every time he tries to Fling-and-kite, Q sustain shrugs off Poison Trail, and R at 6 pins him through his slows before he can Insanity Potion away.","late":"After his first big item Singed proxies, scales, and becomes uncatchable — Rylai's and mass HP mean your R gets baited or Flung, so first item and beyond both belong to him.","whys":["Level 1 favours you: Warwick's Q ticks out-trade Singed's early Poison Trail before he has Fling.","Level 2 is skill: his poison chip starts to matter but you still control lane tempo.","Level 3 favours you: W Blood Hunt speed lets you stick to Singed through his Fling-and-run.","Levels 4-5 favour you: Q healing negates Poison Trail and you win every stationary trade.","Level 6 favours you: R Infinite Duress pins him through Mega Adhesive and his Insanity Potion speed.","First item favours Singed: Rylai's and proxying let him kite and out-scale the duel.","2+ items favour Singed: mass HP and slows make him uncatchable and your R easily baited."]},
  {"a":"warwick","b":"sion","win":["Warwick","Skill","Warwick","Warwick","Warwick","Skill","Sion"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"W Blood Hunt speed lets you weave around his slow, unmissable Q Decimating Smash windup — walk out of the charge, then Q Jaws in for a free trade while it's on cooldown."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R Infinite Duress locks Sion out of his own Q charge and E Roar of the Slayer knockback — ult mid-CS and burst him, but respect his passive: killing him revives an angry zombie."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sion stacks armor and HP fast, and his passive death-timer means even a won trade doesn't secure the kill — the lane sits at Skill as his tankiness starts to catch your DPS."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late Sion is a wall of HP with a knock-up Q, a shield W, and a game-ending R Unstoppable Onslaught engage — your single-target damage can't chew through him and you become peel-fodder."}],"wants":{"you":["Sidestep his Q charge with W speed, then all-in the cooldown","Save R for after his E and Q are committed","Kill him before his passive revive can trade back"],"foe":["Land a fully-charged Q Decimating Smash to stun and flip the trade","Stack armor/HP and use W shield to blunt your Q burst","Engage or peel with R Unstoppable Onslaught in teamfights"]},"early":"Level 1 you win: your Q ticks beat his slow melee poke and he telegraphs everything. Level 2 is Skill — a landed charged Q stun can swing a trade hard, so respect the windup.","mid":"Levels 3-6 are yours. Blood Hunt speed lets you juke the Q charge and punish it on cooldown, Q sustain keeps you healthy, and R at 6 pins him through his knockups — just don't int into his passive revive.","late":"By first item Sion's armor and HP stacking pull the lane to Skill, and with two items his tankiness plus his engage/peel ult outscale you — your DPS can't kill him fast and he flips fights.","whys":["Level 1 favours you: Warwick's Q ticks out-trade Sion's slow early poke.","Level 2 is skill: a fully-charged Q Decimating Smash stun can swing the trade his way.","Level 3 favours you: W Blood Hunt speed lets you sidestep the Q charge and punish its cooldown.","Levels 4-5 favour you: Q sustain and speed win every trade where he misses his charge.","Level 6 favours you: R Infinite Duress pins Sion through his knockups for a burst window.","First item is skill: Sion's armor/HP stacking and passive revive start neutralizing your kills.","2+ items favour Sion: mass tankiness plus his engage ult outscale your single-target DPS."]},
  {"a":"warwick","b":"swain","win":["Warwick","Skill","Warwick","Swain","Warwick","Swain","Swain"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"W Blood Hunt speed lets you dodge his W Vision of Empire zone and close before he lands E Nevermove root — but the moment his E pull connects he burst-heals off you, so bait it first."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R Infinite Duress locks Swain in place, yet his R Demonic Ascension sustain and Q barrage can out-heal your burst if he's already ramped — ult him early in a trade, not late."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With Rylai's and a Blackfire/health item Swain's E root plus R drain out-sustains your DPS in a straight fight — the lane tilts to him as his AoE heal outpaces your damage."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late Swain is an unkillable AoE drain-tank: land E on you and his R heals through your ult, so you can't solo him and he zones you out of every fight."}],"wants":{"you":["Sidestep his E Nevermove with W speed, then all-in","Ult Swain before his R Demonic Ascension ramps its heal","Kill him early before he stacks HP and drain"],"foe":["Land E Nevermove root to pull you in and start the drain","Ramp R Demonic Ascension so your burst just heals him","Zone the wave with W Vision of Empire and Q poke"]},"early":"Level 1 you win: your Q ticks beat his slow Q barrage before he has E to root you. Level 2 is Skill — his poke and W zone start contesting the wave.","mid":"Level 3 is yours with Blood Hunt speed to dodge E and punish, but Levels 4-5 go to Swain — once he can reliably land E Nevermove the pull-plus-drain flips trades. Level 6 is yours if you ult him before his R ramps; catch him early and burst before the heal snowballs.","late":"After his first item Swain's E-into-R drain out-sustains your damage, and by two items he's an unkillable AoE heal-tank who zones you off every objective — the lane belongs to him.","whys":["Level 1 favours you: Warwick's Q ticks out-trade Swain's slow early poke before he has E.","Level 2 is skill: his Q barrage and W zone start contesting the wave.","Level 3 favours you: W Blood Hunt speed lets you dodge E Nevermove and punish on cooldown.","Levels 4-5 favour Swain: a reliable E root pull plus his drain flips trades in his favor.","Level 6 favours you: R Infinite Duress bursts him if you ult before his R Demonic Ascension ramps.","First item favours Swain: Rylai's and R drain out-sustain your DPS in a straight fight.","2+ items favour Swain: unkillable AoE drain-tank who zones you out of every fight."]},
  {"a":"warwick","b":"sylas","win":["Warwick","Skill","Warwick","Warwick","Skill","Warwick","Warwick"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"W Blood Hunt speed lets you dodge his E2 Abscond/Abduct chain-pull and Q Chain Lash, then Q Jaws in — his lifesteal-heal off you means you must trade when his Q is on cooldown."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R Infinite Duress pins Sylas so he can't Abscond dash away, but if he steals your ult (or a better one) the fight shifts — bait his stolen R before you commit yours."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You spike harder into a squishy Sylas at first item: your R chunk plus Q sustain out-duels his shield-heal reset if you catch him after Abscond is down."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late you still win the isolated 1v1 — Sylas is squishy and once his mobility is on cooldown your R chains him down before his W heal can save him."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge his E chain with W speed, then all-in on his cooldowns","Force his stolen R out before you commit Infinite Duress","Isolate him away from his team to secure the 1v1"],"foe":["Poke with Q Chain Lash and heal off you with W","Steal a game-changing ult and dash out with E Abscond","Kite your R window until his mobility comes back up"]},"early":"Level 1 you win: your Q ticks beat his mana-hungry early poke. Level 2 is Skill — his Q Chain Lash and W heal let him trade back if you facecheck.","mid":"Levels 3-4 are yours with Blood Hunt speed to dodge his E chain and punish, and Q sustain to shrug his poke. Level 5 is Skill as his combo comes online, but you flip Level 6 by pinning him through his dash with R before he can Abscond.","late":"First item and beyond stay yours: Sylas is squishy, and once you isolate him and his mobility is down your R plus Q melt him before his W shield-heal resets.","whys":["Level 1 favours you: Warwick's Q ticks out-trade Sylas's mana-hungry early poke.","Level 2 is skill: his Q Chain Lash and W heal let him trade back on a facecheck.","Level 3 favours you: W Blood Hunt speed lets you dodge his E chain and punish cooldowns.","Levels 4-5 are mixed but Level 5 is skill: his full combo comes online and can trade evenly.","Level 6 favours you: R Infinite Duress pins him through Abscond before he can escape.","First item favours you: your R chunk plus Q sustain out-duel his squishy shield-heal reset.","2+ items favour you: isolated and low on mobility, Sylas melts to your R before W can save him."]},
  {"a":"warwick","b":"tahmkench","win":["Warwick","Skill","Warwick","Warwick","Warwick","Skill","Tahm Kench"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"W Blood Hunt speed sticks you on Kench, and Q Jaws sustain shrugs his Q Tongue Lash poke — punish him whenever his Q slow is on cooldown before he can stack passive on you."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R Infinite Duress pins him so he can't W Abyssal Dive out, but respect his W self-peel and grey-health passive shield — burst him before three Q stacks proc his passive stun."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Kench builds HP and his passive grey-health regen makes trades sticky; the lane sits at Skill as his tankiness and self-sustain start eating your DPS."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late Tahm Kench is a mountain of HP with W devour peel, grey-health shielding, and a passive stun — your single-target damage can't kill him and he saves allies from your R."}],"wants":{"you":["Stick with W speed and trade when his Q Tongue Lash is down","Burst him before three passive stacks proc the stun","All-in early before his HP stacking outpaces you"],"foe":["Land Q Tongue Lash to slow and stack passive toward the stun","Use W Abyssal Dive to escape or peel with self-devour","Stack HP and grey-health to out-sustain your trades"]},"early":"Level 1 you win: your Q ticks out-trade his slow Q poke. Level 2 is Skill — his Q slow and passive stacking start to bite if you overstay in a trade.","mid":"Levels 3-6 are yours. Blood Hunt speed keeps you glued to him, Q sustain beats his Tongue Lash chip, and R at 6 pins him through W Abyssal Dive — just burst before his passive stacks to three and stuns you.","late":"By first item his HP and grey-health regen pull the lane to Skill, and with two items he's a self-peeling HP tank whose devour and passive stun outscale you — your DPS can't break him.","whys":["Level 1 favours you: Warwick's Q ticks out-trade Tahm Kench's slow early poke.","Level 2 is skill: his Q Tongue Lash slow and passive stacking start to punish overstays.","Level 3 favours you: W Blood Hunt speed keeps you glued to Kench for trades.","Levels 4-5 favour you: Q sustain beats his Tongue Lash chip and you win stationary trades.","Level 6 favours you: R Infinite Duress pins him through W Abyssal Dive for a burst window.","First item is skill: his HP stacking and grey-health regen start out-sustaining your trades.","2+ items favour Tahm Kench: mass HP, self-peel devour, and passive stun outscale your DPS."]},
  {"a":"warwick","b":"teemo","win":["Warwick","Skill","Warwick","Teemo","Warwick","Teemo","Teemo"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"W Blood Hunt speed closes the gap before Teemo can kite, and Q Jaws sustain heals his auto poison poke — all-in whenever his Q Blinding Dart is on cooldown, since blind neuters your autos."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R Infinite Duress is un-blindable (it's a channel, not an auto) so you can pin Teemo through his Q Blinding Dart — ult him the instant he steps up to poke."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Once Teemo has Liandry's/Nashor's and shroom control the lane flips: his DoT poke and R Noxious Trap zones out-damage your sustain and blind shuts your resets."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late Teemo is a kiting DoT machine — shroom walls block your W chase, Blinding Dart cancels your auto damage, and his poison out-sustains you from range you can't close."}],"wants":{"you":["All-in with W speed while his Q Blinding Dart is down","Use R Infinite Duress to pin him through the blind","Kill him early before shrooms and Liandry's come online"],"foe":["Blind your autos with Q so your Q-empowered hits whiff","Kite with move-speed passive and poison DoT chip","Wall off with R Noxious Trap shrooms to block your chase"]},"early":"Level 1 you win: your Q ticks out-trade his single auto before he can kite. Level 2 is Skill — his Blinding Dart and poison start to chip and his move speed makes him slippery.","mid":"Level 3 is yours with Blood Hunt speed to catch him, but Level 4 flips to Teemo as his poke and blind uptime grow. Level 5 swings back to you, and at 6 your un-blindable R lets you pin him through Blinding Dart for a kill.","late":"After his first item Teemo's DoT, shroom zoning, and blind out-scale your sustain — first item and beyond both belong to him as he kites you from a range you can't close.","whys":["Level 1 favours you: Warwick's Q ticks out-trade Teemo's single early auto.","Level 2 is skill: his Q Blinding Dart and poison chip start to matter and he's slippery.","Level 3 favours you: W Blood Hunt speed lets you close and all-in before he kites.","Levels 4-5 favour Teemo: growing blind uptime and poke let him win the chip trades.","Level 6 favours you: R Infinite Duress is un-blindable and pins Teemo through his Q.","First item favours Teemo: Liandry's DoT and shroom control out-damage your sustain.","2+ items favour Teemo: kiting poison and shroom walls keep you out of range entirely."]},
  {"a":"warwick","b":"trundle","win":["Trundle","Skill","Skill","Skill","Trundle","Skill","Warwick"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Trundle's Chomp (Q) shreds your armor and heals him off every auto, so trading straight up early feeds his sustain; poke with Q Jaws and reset rather than sitting in his bite range."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Trundle's Subjugate (R) rips a chunk of your resistances and max health right when you want to all-in with Infinite Duress, so bait his ult or wait it out before you commit."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With Blood Hunt lifesteal and a completed bruiser item you finally out-heal his Chomp in extended fights; look for a below-50% enemy to trigger W's move-speed and lock him with R."},{"when":"Late","text":"Warwick scales into a raid boss with lifesteal and R lockdown while Trundle falls off as a single-target duelist, so drag fights long and hunt low targets across the map."}],"wants":{"you":["Extended fights once your lifesteal and Q healing come online","A sub-50% target to proc Blood Hunt speed and land R","Jungle ganks while his Pillar (E) and R are down"],"foe":["Short bites with Chomp to steal your armor and heal","Landing Subjugate before your all-in to swing the stat gap","Using Pillar (E) to slow you and kite your dash"]},"early":"Trundle owns the first levels: his Chomp shreds your armor, heals him, and gives him attack speed, so a level-1 or level-3 brawl over his Contaminate zone goes his way. Farm with Q Jaws, dodge sitting still in his bite range, and don't int a trade just because you have Eternal Hunger healing.","mid":"By 3-5 it's even skill: your Q sustain and lane presence hold, but his Subjugate at 6 swings a straight duel by stripping your resistances and max HP. Respect that window, ping your jungler, and only commit R when his ult is on cooldown.","late":"Once your first bruiser item and Blood Hunt lifesteal land you out-sustain his Chomp and win extended fights; Trundle is a lane bully who fades while Warwick becomes an unkillable hunter that locks and drags low targets down.","whys":["Trundle's Chomp shreds armor, heals, and grants attack speed, giving him the level-1 edge.","Level 2 is even as both champs are still farming with single abilities and neither commits.","Level 3 stays skill-based once your Q Jaws sustain answers his early bite trades.","Levels 4-5 remain a coinflip of poke and positioning before either ultimate is online.","Trundle's Subjugate at 6 steals your resistances and max health, tipping the all-in to him.","First item is even as your lifesteal starts closing the gap on his Chomp sustain.","With two-plus items your lifesteal, Q healing, and R lockdown let Warwick out-scale the falling-off Trundle."]},
  {"a":"warwick","b":"tryndamere","win":["Warwick","Skill","Warwick","Warwick","Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Before Tryndamere stacks Fury he has no sustain and low damage, so your Q Jaws heal and Eternal Hunger let you win short trades; punish him whenever his Spinning Slash (E) is on cooldown."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Undying Rage (R) makes him unkillable for 5 seconds, so never blow Infinite Duress on him at full Fury; instead trade him down and save your R to peel or lock him after his ult ends."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Once he has crit and Fury sustain he out-duels you in a straight fight; play for shortened trades and hand him to your jungler rather than a solo all-in."},{"when":"Late","text":"Tryndamere scales into a split-push monster who out-DPSes and out-sustains you 1v1; your value shifts to hunting his carries with R and grouping rather than matching his side lane."}],"wants":{"you":["Short trades before he builds Fury and crit","Punishing his Spinning Slash (E) cooldown windows","Ganks while he lacks the stats to fight back"],"foe":["Stacked Fury and crit items for a sustained duel","Saving Undying Rage (R) to survive your all-in","Splitpushing 1v1 where his DPS and heal snowball"]},"early":"Early Tryndamere is weak: no Fury means no sustain and mediocre auto damage, so your Q Jaws heal and passive out-value his pokes and you take the level-1 and level-3/4 windows. Trade when his Spinning Slash (E) is down and deny his Fury generation off minions.","mid":"Levels 4-5 are even as he starts stacking Fury and crit chance, but the fight flips at 6: Undying Rage guarantees five seconds of survival, so a raw Infinite Duress all-in just wastes your ultimate. Bait or wait out his R before committing lockdown.","late":"With crit items and Fury sustain online Tryndamere out-duels you in a straight fight and becomes a split-push threat, so you stop matching him 1v1. Warwick's late value is hunting his backline with R and Blood Hunt speed while your team pressures elsewhere.","whys":["No Fury means no sustain early, so your Q heal and passive win the level-1 trade.","Level 2 is even before either champ has a real all-in threat online.","Level 3 favors you as your Jaws sustain out-values his still-weak, Fury-starved trades.","Levels 4-5 stay yours while he lacks the crit and Fury to punish short trades.","Level 6 is even because Undying Rage negates your all-in but doesn't yet let him kill you.","First item favors Tryndamere as crit and Fury sustain let him out-duel you straight up.","With two-plus items his crit DPS and unkillable ult make him the stronger 1v1 splitpusher."]},
  {"a":"warwick","b":"urgot","win":["Urgot","Urgot","Urgot","Urgot","Urgot","Urgot","Warwick"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Urgot's Purge (W) melts you the instant you walk in, and Corrosive Charge (Q) plus his passive shotgun legs zone you off the wave; don't dash in on Q Jaws expecting to trade, you'll lose every exchange."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Fear Beyond Death (R) executes you below the health threshold and drags you in, so keep your bars high and never all-in with Infinite Duress into a healthy Urgot who can just W-Purge and flip you."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With Bami/tank items Urgot's Purge does even more sustained damage and his shield off Q keeps him healthy, so keep farming safely and wait for jungle pressure instead of soloing him."},{"when":"Late","text":"Warwick finally out-scales: with full lifesteal and R lockdown you can flash-R him from fog before he lines up Purge, and team fights let you dodge his slow, clunky shotgun legs."}],"wants":{"you":["Late-game fights where lifesteal and R flanks bypass his poke","Flanking with Blood Hunt speed so he can't line up Purge","Jungle ganks to punish his low early mobility"],"foe":["Standing to W-Purge you the moment you enter melee","Landing Corrosive Charge (Q) and shotgun legs to zone the wave","Executing you with Fear Beyond Death (R) after Purge chunks"]},"early":"This is a losing lane early: Urgot's Purge shreds you the second you step up, Corrosive Charge and his passive legs zone you off farm, and you have no way to trade back through his range. Give up nothing by dashing in on Q Jaws, farm at max range, and accept you'll be down CS.","mid":"It stays rough through 6: Fear Beyond Death executes you below the threshold and yanks you in, so a healthy Urgot beats your Infinite Duress all-in outright when he Purges and flips it. Keep your HP high, ward for his jungler, and lean on your own jungle to make plays.","late":"Warwick's scaling finally pulls ahead with two-plus items: full lifesteal and R lockdown let you flash-R or flank him from fog before he lines up Purge, and messy team fights punish his slow shotgun-leg positioning. Hunt him from angles rather than facechecking his lane.","whys":["Urgot's Purge and shotgun legs out-range and out-damage you from level 1.","Level 2 stays his as Corrosive Charge and Purge zone you off the wave.","Level 3 favors Urgot because you still can't trade through his sustained Purge damage.","Levels 4-5 remain his as his poke and shield keep him healthy while you fall behind.","At 6 Fear Beyond Death executes you and beats your all-in, keeping the edge his.","First item favors Urgot as tank stats and Purge scaling deepen his lane dominance.","With two-plus items Warwick's lifesteal, R lockdown, and flank angles finally out-scale him."]},
  {"a":"warwick","b":"vayne","win":["Vayne","Vayne","Vayne","Vayne","Skill","Vayne","Vayne"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Vayne's Condemn (E) knocks you out of Q Jaws range and can stun you into the wall, while Tumble (Q) resets her spacing every trade; if she lands E you lose the exchange, so bait it before you dash."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Final Hour plus Tumble stealth lets her vanish from your Infinite Duress channel, and Silver Bolts true damage melts your health bar; only all-in when her Condemn is on cooldown and she's cornered."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With attack speed and Silver Bolts online her true-damage DPS out-races your lifesteal, so stop soloing her and collapse with your jungler instead."},{"when":"Late","text":"Vayne is a hyper-carry who shreds tanks and kites you with Condemn and Final Hour stealth; your only path is flanking with R from fog so she can't Tumble or E away before you lock her."}],"wants":{"you":["Baiting out her Condemn (E) before you commit a dash","Flanking from fog so she can't Tumble away from R","Ganks while she has no attack-speed items"],"foe":["Landing Condemn (E) to stun you into a wall","Kiting with Tumble (Q) and Final Hour stealth","Stacking Silver Bolts true damage in extended fights"]},"early":"Vayne wins the early lane: Condemn knocks you out of your Q Jaws range or stuns you into a wall, and Tumble constantly re-spaces so you never get a clean trade. Don't dash in blindly, force her to waste E on a fake commit, and just farm safely while you're the weaker champ.","mid":"Level 5-6 is briefly even skill as your all-in power peaks, but Final Hour and Tumble stealth let her disappear mid-Infinite-Duress, and Silver Bolts true damage chews through your HP. Only commit R when her Condemn is down and she has no room to kite.","late":"Vayne scales into a true-damage hyper-carry who shreds your bruiser build and kites you endlessly with Condemn and stealth. Warwick's only real angle is a fog flank with Blood Hunt speed to lock her before she Tumbles or E's away; otherwise let your team peel and you hunt other targets.","whys":["Vayne's Condemn and Tumble spacing beat your short-range trades from level 1.","Level 2 stays hers as Condemn threatens to stun you out of every commit.","Level 3 favors Vayne because Tumble re-spacing denies your Q Jaws engage.","Levels 4-5 remain hers as her kite tools out-trade your dash-in.","Level 5 is a brief skill window where your peak all-in can catch a mispositioned Vayne.","At 6 Final Hour stealth and Silver Bolts let her escape your R and out-DPS you.","With two-plus items her true-damage hyper-carry scaling and kiting keep the matchup hers."]},
  {"a":"warwick","b":"vladimir","win":["Warwick","Skill","Warwick","Warwick","Skill","Vladimir","Vladimir"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Vladimir is weak and mana-less-but-health-costed early, so your Q Jaws heal and Eternal Hunger win short trades; punish him right after he uses Sanguine Pool (W) since it's on a long cooldown and leaves him exposed."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your Infinite Duress all-in is strong here, but Sanguine Pool untargets him mid-channel, so time R for the moment his W is down and Blood Hunt is active for the speed and heal."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Once Vladimir stacks health and ability haste his Transfusion (Q) sustain and Pool up-time out-heal your damage; stop soloing him and look to the map instead."},{"when":"Late","text":"Vladimir becomes an AoE teamfight monster with Hemoplague (R) amp and constant Pool escapes; your job is to R his backline in fights, not to duel his self-sustaining, untargetable frontline."}],"wants":{"you":["Short trades before he stacks health and haste","Punishing the long Sanguine Pool (W) cooldown","All-in with R while his Pool is unavailable"],"foe":["Scaling health and haste to out-heal you with Transfusion (Q)","Using Sanguine Pool (W) to dodge your R channel","Teamfights where Hemoplague (R) and AoE reign"]},"early":"Vladimir is soft early: his Transfusion costs health and his damage is low, so your Q Jaws heal and passive let you win short trades and deny his farm. The key window is right after Sanguine Pool — it's a long cooldown, so if he burns it to dodge, step up and punish before it's back.","mid":"Levels 4-5 are even as he starts stacking, and your level-6 all-in is real, but Pool untargets him mid-Infinite-Duress and wastes your ult if you mistime it. Commit R only when his W is down and Blood Hunt is up for the extra speed and lifesteal.","late":"After his first health/haste item Vladimir's Transfusion sustain and Pool up-time out-heal your DPS, and he snowballs into an AoE teamfight threat with Hemoplague's damage amp. Stop dueling him; use R to lock his carries in fights while your team handles his untouchable frontline.","whys":["Vladimir's health-cost Transfusion and low early damage let your Q heal win level 1.","Level 2 is even before either champ has a committal trade pattern online.","Level 3 favors you as your Jaws sustain out-trades his weak early poke.","Levels 4-5 stay yours while he still lacks the health and haste to out-sustain you.","Level 5-6 is even because your all-in is strong but Sanguine Pool can dodge it.","First item favors Vladimir as Transfusion sustain and Pool up-time out-heal your damage.","With two-plus items his AoE teamfight scaling and Hemoplague amp take over the game."]},
  {"a":"warwick","b":"volibear","win":["Warwick","Skill","Volibear","Volibear","Volibear","Volibear","Warwick"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Once Volibear has Thundering Smash (Q) stun and Frenzied Maul (W) he out-trades you: his W heals and shreds, his Q stuns if he closes distance, so don't stand still trading and bait his Q by moving unpredictably."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Stormbringer (R) makes him near-unstoppable, shields him, and disables your towers; never all-in with Infinite Duress into his up R, and respect that he wins the extended fight through his W sustain."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Volibear's bruiser spike with W heal and R shield out-sustains your damage in a straight duel, so keep farming safely and defer to jungle collapses rather than soloing him."},{"when":"Late","text":"Warwick out-scales into the late game: with full lifesteal and R lockdown you can flank his backline and drag targets down, whereas Voli is a front-to-back diver you can peel and kite in fights."}],"wants":{"you":["Level-1 cheese before his Q stun is online","Late fights where lifesteal and R flanks out-scale him","Baiting his Thundering Smash (Q) so he can't stun-engage"],"foe":["Landing Thundering Smash (Q) stun to lock a trade","Out-sustaining you with Frenzied Maul (W) heals","All-in under Stormbringer (R) shield and tower disable"]},"early":"Level 1 is yours before Volibear has his stun: your Q Jaws and passive win the opening trade if he steps up. But once he hits Thundering Smash and Frenzied Maul at 2-3 the lane flips — his W heals and shreds while his Q stuns any close-range fight, so stop trading toe-to-toe and juke his Q with erratic movement.","mid":"Levels 3 through 6 belong to Volibear: his W sustain out-heals your trades and Stormbringer at 6 gives a shield, near-unstoppable dash, and tower disable that beats your Infinite Duress all-in. Don't commit R into his up ultimate; farm safe and wait for your jungler.","late":"The matchup swings back to you with two-plus items: full lifesteal and R lockdown let you flank Voli's team and drag his carries down, while he's a predictable front-line diver you can peel and kite. Play for late team fights, not the mid-game solo duel.","whys":["Level 1 is yours before Volibear's Q stun and W sustain come online.","Level 2 is even as he picks up his kit but can't yet out-trade you cleanly.","Level 3 favors Volibear once Frenzied Maul heal and Thundering Smash stun are online.","Levels 4-5 stay his as his W sustain out-heals your extended trades.","At 6 Stormbringer's shield, unstoppable dash, and tower disable beat your all-in.","First item favors Volibear as his bruiser sustain out-duels you straight up.","With two-plus items Warwick's lifesteal and R flanks out-scale his front-line diving."]},
  {"a":"warwick","b":"wukong","win":["Warwick","Skill","Skill","Skill","Warwick","Wukong","Wukong"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Wukong's Warrior Trickster (W) clone and stealth let him bait your Q Jaws dash and disengage, while Crushing Blow (Q) armor-shred plus Nimbus Strike (E) gap-close even the trades; watch for the decoy before you commit."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your all-in is strong here, but Cyclone (R) knocks you up and out of Infinite Duress, so only commit R when his ult is down; if you catch him without W or R he's dead to your lockdown."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Wukong's burst spike with armor-pen and Q shred out-trades you in a straight duel, and his W clone escapes your follow-up, so play safe and set up ganks instead of soloing."},{"when":"Late","text":"Wukong scales into a teamfight bruiser whose Cyclone displaces your whole team; your job is to R-lock him or his carry from a flank rather than dueling him where his W and R reset the fight."}],"wants":{"you":["Level-1 and level-6 windows where your all-in beats his cooldowns","Catching him with W clone and Cyclone (R) on cooldown","Ganks while his armor-pen spike isn't online"],"foe":["Baiting your dash with Warrior Trickster (W) clone","Winning trades with Crushing Blow (Q) armor shred","Displacing you out of R with Cyclone (R)"]},"early":"Level 1 is yours: your Q Jaws heal and passive beat Wukong before his kit comes online. Levels 2-4 settle into even skill — his W clone and stealth can bait your dash and his Q shreds your armor, so the trades come down to reading his decoy and not chasing the clone.","mid":"Level 6 swings back to you: your Infinite Duress all-in is strong, and if you catch Wukong with Warrior Trickster and Cyclone on cooldown he simply dies to your lockdown. Just respect that his R knocks you out of the channel, so only commit when his ult is down.","late":"After his first item Wukong's armor-pen burst and Q shred out-trade you in a straight duel, and his W clone escapes your follow-up, so stop soloing him. In team fights his Cyclone displaces your whole line — your value is flanking to R-lock him or his carry rather than dueling where his W and R reset everything.","whys":["Level 1 is yours as your Q heal and passive beat Wukong before his kit is online.","Level 2 is even skill as his W clone and stealth start to answer your trades.","Level 3 stays even with his Q armor shred trading against your Jaws sustain.","Levels 4-5 remain a skill matchup of reading his decoy versus your dash timing.","Level 6 favors you since your all-in kills him when his W and R are down.","First item favors Wukong as armor-pen burst and Q shred out-trade you straight up.","With two-plus items his teamfight Cyclone displacement and W escapes out-scale your solo threat."]},
  {"a":"warwick","b":"yasuo","win":["Warwick","Warwick","Warwick","Warwick","Warwick","Yasuo","Yasuo"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Once Q Jaws of the Beast heals off minions and W Blood Hunt is up, walk him down every time his E Sweeping Blade is on cooldown; he has no reliable way to trade back through your sustain."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Yasuo's R Last Breath comes online and gives him a burst window off any airborne CC, so respect ganks — but 1v1 your R Infinite Duress still beats his kit if you land it clean."},{"when":"1st item","text":"His first crit item (IE or Shieldbow rush) is the point his all-in damage spikes past your Q healing; stop face-tanking and use E Primal Howl's fear to break his tempo."},{"when":"Late","text":"With crit stacked and Wind Wall up on cooldown, Yasuo out-DPSes you in extended fights, so pick him with R engage from fog rather than dueling him even."}],"wants":{"you":["W Blood Hunt active on a low-HP Yasuo to chase him down","fighting while his E Sweeping Blade dashes are on cooldown","short trades where Q sustain refills what his Q tornado poke chips"],"foe":["stacked crit so his auto-attacks out-damage your Q heal","a minion wave to dash through with E for kiting distance","a knock-up from your jungler to combo into R Last Breath"]},"early":"You dominate levels 1-3: Yasuo's early Q Steel Tempest and E Sweeping Blade poke does little against Q Jaws of the Beast healing, and once W Blood Hunt marks him you win any short trade. Don't let him free-farm with E dashes on the wave — step up whenever his dash is down.","mid":"Through levels 4-6 you keep the edge because his Wind Wall only blocks projectiles, not your point-blank R Infinite Duress, and your sustain refills any tornado chip. Look to force all-ins while his E is on cooldown and W is active.","late":"Once Yasuo finishes a crit item the fight flips: his sustained auto DPS plus Wind Wall and R Last Breath off any knock-up outscale your dueling. Play for R engages from fog and let your team follow rather than trading blows straight up.","whys":["Warwick-favoured: Q Jaws healing shrugs off Yasuo's level-1 Steel Tempest poke.","Warwick-favoured: W Blood Hunt lets you punish him the moment his E dash is down.","Warwick-favoured: point-blank R Infinite Duress ignores his Wind Wall so short trades are yours.","Warwick-favoured: your sustain keeps refilling faster than his tornado poke chips you.","Warwick-favoured: at 6 your R still cleanly beats his kit 1v1 before crit comes online.","Yasuo-favoured: his first crit item pushes auto DPS past your Q heal in all-ins.","Yasuo-favoured: stacked crit plus Wind Wall and R Last Breath outscale you in extended fights."]},
  {"a":"warwick","b":"yone","win":["Warwick","Skill","Warwick","Warwick","Warwick","Yone","Yone"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"With Q Jaws of the Beast healing and W Blood Hunt speed, walk Yone down whenever his E Soul Unbound is on cooldown — he can't snap back to safety and your sustain wins the trade."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Yone's R Fate Sealed knocks you toward him for a burst combo, but 1v1 your R Infinite Duress suppresses him out of his Q3 knock-up window if you open with it."},{"when":"1st item","text":"His first crit/on-hit item (Immortal Shieldbow or crit) is when his mixed-damage all-in outpaces your Q heal; stop face-tanking and save E Primal Howl to fear his Q3."},{"when":"Late","text":"With items Yone's E Soul Unbound lets him deal damage then rewind to full position and health-state, so he wins extended duels — pick him with R engage instead."}],"wants":{"you":["W Blood Hunt on a low Yone to run him down before E resets","trading while his E Soul Unbound and Q3 knock-up are on cooldown","short Q-healed trades that beat his early Q Mortal Steel poke"],"foe":["a completed crit or on-hit item so his mixed damage beats your heal","E Soul Unbound up to deal damage then rewind out of your R","landing Q3 knock-up or R Fate Sealed to open a burst combo"]},"early":"Level 1-2 is skill-dependent: Yone's Q Mortal Steel poke and range let him harass, but your Q Jaws of the Beast heal keeps you even if you don't walk into his Q3 knock-up. Farm safely and don't get clipped by his empowered third Q.","mid":"From level 3 on you take over — W Blood Hunt speed lets you close and force trades whenever his E Soul Unbound is down, and your sustain out-values his poke. Punish every E he spends offensively because he can't rewind and disengage at once.","late":"Once Yone completes an item his kit flips the matchup: E Soul Unbound rewinds his position and health-state after he commits, and crit-backed mixed damage overwhelms your Q heal. Play for R Infinite Duress engages from fog and let your team collapse rather than dueling.","whys":["Warwick-favoured: Q Jaws healing holds level 1 despite Yone's Mortal Steel range.","Skill: his Q3 knock-up poke trades even against your sustain if you misposition.","Warwick-favoured: W Blood Hunt lets you punish every offensive E Soul Unbound.","Warwick-favoured: your Q heal out-values his poke while his rewind is down.","Warwick-favoured: at 6 your R suppresses him out of his combo before crit online.","Yone-favoured: his first crit/on-hit item pushes mixed damage past your heal.","Yone-favoured: E Soul Unbound rewind plus crit outscales you in long duels."]},
  {"a":"warwick","b":"yorick","win":["Warwick","Warwick","Skill","Skill","Yorick","Yorick","Yorick"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Before Yorick has a full ghoul pack, all-in him when his E Mourning Mist is on cooldown — without the slow-mark he can't kite you and your Q heal wins the trade."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Yorick's R Eulogy of the Isles spawns Maiden and a wall of ghouls; once his cage is up he can trap you and let ghouls plus autos shred you, so this is where he takes over."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With his first bruiser item and Maiden pushing, Yorick's ghoul DPS out-damages your sustain and his W Dark Procession cage denies your escape; don't dive the wave."},{"when":"Late","text":"Yorick with full ghouls and Maiden out-DPSes and out-splits you; avoid sidelane duels and instead group where his single-target cage matters less."}],"wants":{"you":["all-in windows when his E Mourning Mist slow-mark is on cooldown","fighting before he has a full ghoul pack stacked","short Q-healed trades in the first three levels"],"foe":["a full ghoul pack plus Maiden to stack damage on you","E Mourning Mist landed so ghouls swarm and slow you","W Dark Procession cage to trap you and deny your escape"]},"early":"You own levels 1-2: without a ghoul pack Yorick relies on E Mourning Mist and autos, and your Q Jaws of the Beast heal beats his early trades. Punish him hard before his ghouls come online and W Blood Hunt lets you chase.","mid":"Levels 3-5 turn skill-based as his ghoul pack fills out — he uses E to mark you and swarm with ghouls, so only commit when his E is down. If you let him stack ghouls the trade math flips against your sustain.","late":"From level 6 Yorick takes control: R Eulogy of the Isles adds Maiden and a ghoul wall, and his W Dark Procession cage can trap you for a full ghoul-plus-auto burst. Stop dueling him in the sidelane and group so his single-target kit matters less; his split pressure outscales your dueling.","whys":["Warwick-favoured: Q Jaws healing beats Yorick's level-1 trades before ghouls.","Warwick-favoured: at 2 you still win short trades while his ghoul pack is thin.","Skill: once his ghoul pack builds, trades hinge on dodging his E Mourning Mist.","Skill: E-cooldown windows are even — commit only when his mark is down.","Yorick-favoured: R Eulogy adds Maiden and a ghoul wall that overwhelm your heal.","Yorick-favoured: first item plus Maiden ghoul DPS and W cage beat your sustain.","Yorick-favoured: full ghouls and Maiden out-split and out-DPS you late."]},
  {"a":"warwick","b":"zac","win":["Warwick","Skill","Warwick","Warwick","Warwick","Skill","Zac"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Zac heals off his passive blobs, so all-in him after he's spent E Elastic Slingshot or Q Stretching Strikes and before he can pick up blobs — your Q heal plus W Blood Hunt out-sustains him."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Zac's R Let's Bounce brings AoE knock-ups but does little to a 1v1 — your R Infinite Duress still locks him down, so this window stays even-to-yours if you dodge his E engage."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With his first health item Zac's passive blob healing and Q knock-up chains let him tank and reset trades, pulling him back to even against your damage."},{"when":"Late","text":"Fully built, Zac is an unkillable engage tank who bounces in with R and peels — you can't duel him down, so use your R to catch his squishies instead of fighting him."}],"wants":{"you":["all-in after his E Elastic Slingshot and Q are spent and blobs aren't picked up","W Blood Hunt active to out-sustain his passive blob healing","short trades that beat his early poke before he stacks health"],"foe":["a health item so his passive blobs and Q chains reset every trade","picking up passive blobs to heal back the damage you deal","landing E Elastic Slingshot to knock you up and start a chain"]},"early":"Level 1-2 is skill-based: Zac's Q Stretching Strikes has long range and his passive lets him heal off blobs, so short trades can go either way. Keep your Q Jaws of the Beast for the heal and don't eat his E Elastic Slingshot engage.","mid":"Levels 3-5 swing to you — if you all-in right after he uses E and Q, and step on his passive blobs so he can't heal, your Q sustain plus W Blood Hunt speed wins the fight. Deny the blob pickups and he can't reset the trade.","late":"By level 6 Zac's blob healing and Q knock-up chains pull him back to even, and once he has a health item he becomes an unkillable engage tank whose R Let's Bounce peels for his team. Stop trying to duel him and use R Infinite Duress to catch his carries instead.","whys":["Warwick-favoured: Q Jaws healing edges his level-1 trade before blob stacking.","Skill: his long Q range and blob heals make level-2 trades a coin-flip.","Warwick-favoured: all-in after his E/Q spent, denying blobs, wins the fight.","Warwick-favoured: W Blood Hunt sustain out-paces his blob healing here.","Warwick-favoured: at 6 your R still locks him 1v1 despite his R knock-ups.","Skill: a health item and Q chains let his blob healing reset trades to even.","Zac-favoured: fully built he's an unkillable engage tank you can't duel down."]},
  {"a":"warwick","b":"ziggs","win":["Warwick","Skill","Warwick","Ziggs","Warwick","Ziggs","Ziggs"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Ziggs pokes with Q Bouncing Bomb from max range, but with W Blood Hunt speed and Q Jaws healing you can close the gap when his Q is on cooldown and force a losing trade for him."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R Infinite Duress is untargetable dash-suppression that ignores his W Satchel Charge knockback if you commit cleanly — a landed R deletes him, so this window is yours."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Once Ziggs has Luden's or his first AP item, his Q poke and W self-knockback disengage let him zone you off the wave and chip you down before you reach him."},{"when":"Late","text":"With items Ziggs kites you forever — W Satchel bumps you away, E Hexplosive Minefield slows, and his burst outranges your all-in, so flank with R from fog and never facecheck his poke."}],"wants":{"you":["W Blood Hunt speed to close on him while his Q Bouncing Bomb is down","a clean R Infinite Duress that ignores his W Satchel knockback","short gap-closes that punish his weak melee-range trading"],"foe":["a completed AP item so Q poke and burst chip you before you reach him","W Satchel Charge up to self-knockback away from your engage","E Hexplosive Minefield placed to slow your approach and kite you"]},"early":"Level 1-2 is skill-based: Ziggs zones with Q Bouncing Bomb and you take chip closing the gap, but Q Jaws of the Beast healing keeps you healthy if you dodge his bombs. Farm what you safely can and wait for your speed spike.","mid":"Level 3 and again at 6 favour you — W Blood Hunt lets you sprint him down when his Q is on cooldown, and R Infinite Duress suppresses him through his W Satchel self-knockback if you commit clean. Land one all-in and he can't survive it.","late":"Level 4-5 and everything past his first item swing to Ziggs: his AP poke chips you before you arrive, W Satchel bumps you out of range, and E Hexplosive Minefield slows your chase. Don't facecheck his line — flank with R from fog or let your team engage first, because he out-kites and out-ranges your straight-up dive.","whys":["Warwick-favoured: Q Jaws healing shrugs off his level-1 Bouncing Bomb chip.","Skill: closing distance on his Q poke is a trade-off both ways at level 2.","Warwick-favoured: W Blood Hunt speed lets you punish him when his Q is down.","Ziggs-favoured: by 4-5 his Q poke and W disengage zone you off the wave.","Warwick-favoured: at 6 a clean R suppresses him through his Satchel knockback.","Ziggs-favoured: his first AP item chips you down before your dive lands.","Ziggs-favoured: full items let him kite you forever with W, E, and Q range."]}
